## Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for the PingNexa project.

### Summary of Changes

The project already had the `@vercel/analytics` package installed (version 2.0.1) and imported in the root layout file, but the Analytics component was not being rendered. I've now completed the integration by adding the Analytics component to the application.

### Modified Files

**project/src/app/layout.tsx**
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag (after the provider components)
- Also added `<SpeedInsights />` component which was imported but not rendered
- Both components are placed at the end of the body element, following Next.js App Router best practices

**project/package-lock.json**
- Updated after running `npm install` to ensure dependencies are properly installed

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Web Analytics documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart):

1. **Package**: The `@vercel/analytics@2.0.1` package was already installed
2. **Framework**: Next.js App Router (detected from the presence of `src/app/layout.tsx`)
3. **Integration**: Added the `<Analytics />` component from `@vercel/analytics/next` to the root layout
4. **Placement**: Components are placed inside the `<body>` tag for optimal tracking

### Next Steps

To complete the analytics setup:

1. **Deploy to Vercel**: The analytics will be automatically enabled when deployed to Vercel
2. **Enable in Dashboard**: Ensure Web Analytics is enabled in the Vercel project dashboard under Analytics
3. **Verification**: After deployment, verify tracking is working by checking the browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/...`

### Notes

- The build process encountered a pre-existing Firebase configuration error (invalid API key) which is unrelated to the Analytics integration
- Both `@vercel/analytics` and `@vercel/speed-insights` are now properly integrated
- The implementation follows Next.js App Router conventions and Vercel's official documentation
- Analytics will only collect data when the application is deployed on Vercel's platform
